        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Power Line Resiliency Act</b></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Energy (DOE) to establish a five-year program to provide grants to electric utilities to (1) improve the performance or efficiency of a power line, (2) make a power line more resilient to an extreme weather event, or (3) otherwise ensure that an end-user has access to electricity during an extreme weather event.</p> <p>DOE must prioritize providing grants to electric utilities that sell electricity in an area that has a history of extreme weather events.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
